paragraph.text:
the Federal
			 Government and State governments have encouraged hardrock mining in the United
			 States through a wide variety of laws, policies, and actions;

mining operations
			 produce metals and minerals that have important social benefits and
			 values;

many areas in the
			 United States at which historic mining operations took place are now the
			 locations of inactive and abandoned mine sites;

many of the
			 historic mining sites have polluted the environment for more than a century
			 and, unless remedied, will continue to do so indefinitely;

unabated
			 discharges from inactive and abandoned mines will continue to pollute surface
			 water, groundwater, and soils;

the potential obligations, requirements, and liabilities under the
Federal Water Pollution Control Act
( 33 U.S.C. 1251 et seq. ) that may attach to Good Samaritans as the result of the conduct by the Good Samaritans of remediation activities can dissuade potential Good Samaritans from acting for the public good;

